\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid11620878 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You were a tub filler?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 I were a tub-}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9664688\charrsid3812201 drawer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  and you have to fill them and draw - h
ave to fill and draw 'em out. If - if your men hadn't filled your tub when you went in you help to fill it - it fill and then had to draw it out and take it so far with it and hooked 'em on and sent it to the pit you see. But first starting my days in a p
it it were me birthday. I were thirteen year old and was down pit. When I had it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 On your thirteenth birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Thirteenth birthday I had it down the mines.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 This was your first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 That - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What had you done before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Oh at half time twelve - twelve year old - helping to dress tripe and make black puddings. Two shillings a week and me breakfast - and me breakfast. You know what me breakfast was? Well you know what they put in black pudding, they put them groats - wha
t they call groats, a kind of a wheat - a kind of wheat. Well them was boiled in boil - in a bag in a boiler, then I had some of them and some - sugar and milk on and very good and that were me breakfast and I had two shilling a week. That were all. But -
 I used go and help at night and daytime as a boy, I did all sorts as a boy, had to do for a butty - jam butty. I walked a mile and a half for jam butty you know. Well - I've done a mile and a half for a jam butty and didn't I know it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You were so poor were you as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 We were as poor as }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9664688\charrsid3812201 Lazarus}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  and I remembered this, I were only young and mother - me mother had uncle called Uncle Sam on lower side of Moses Gate station, and we lived right at top end of the Little Hulton and I remember same as
 it were today, two in the carriage, me and t'other brother at each side walking with her. All way to Moses Gate for our tea for to see Uncle Sam, and walk back other side and I've walked in many procession with me clogs on - couldn't help it, I had no sh
oes. They were wicked days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 How did you get this first job?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What - do you mean -?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 When you were making black puddings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well he were an old man and his wife had a shop across from where we lived and I used to run errands for him for an
ything, you know. Well then I never were away I'd now where to go. We were only on three days a week in the pits you know, that's what kills us, that what killed us, there were too many pits. There were 10 pits in 2 miles and they could not sell the coal 
in the summer. So we were on slack time you see. Well I never left there. I'd get plenty of good food, - I'd more tea times than teas at home you know. I never had no supper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Some days you never got anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No. But what I'd scramble. I - I'd ge
t a bit because I were there - we never saw no suppers. Oh. No, never see no suppers - never thought - but I was dragged up and me father and mother wasn't happy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Why weren't they happy, do you think it was poverty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Yes, they was, my father worked at Tyldesley Bonds and he had a good place at -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Tyldesley?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Bonds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What's that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9664688\charrsid3812201 Well it's Tyldesley, it's the other side of Little Hulton - Atherton, Tyldesley, then comes Little Hulton you see.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 They're more or less all together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 That's it aye. Well he were - he had a good place in the pit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 He was in the pit too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Oh, yes. Fifteen shillings a week he had. Now remember we paid three and four rent. And there were six of us. Now start reckoning up now. You had - you paid for your own doctor you know. You had your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9664688\charrsid3812201 doctor\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  bills coming, between children - then }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9664688\charrsid3812201 there\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  somebody ill. You might have two or three piled up (bills he means) and frightened of sending for him. Then you'd have a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9664688\charrsid3812201 doctor\rquote s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  man coming over for it every week and if you'd give him 3d. he were laughing. He were laughing. Oh yes, Gods, truth on the dot he'd come, any time, on those terms, rain or snow he'd come.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Where was your father from originally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Little Hulton. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Where was your mother from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Little Hulton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did she do a job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did her do a job, in my days I've seen her wash for two or three people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 To help the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Carry through. Carry through. Well then eventually you know it - were all started w
orking and things were a bit brighter and I had a brother killed in the pit - nearly fifteen year old. Nearly - going in his fifteenth birthday. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What happened to him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9664688\charrsid3812201 Well - he - he worked at the same pit as I but not in t' same place like 
and he was supposed fetch these stubs as were fastened - was coming into the pit and then when he got to the opt of the - with the hill he had to unhook it, and let them run down under them and a wagon run over him, he were dead and - I never saw him. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye. Nearly fifteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What did your mother do before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 She were a weaver.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 And she took in washing after your children came along?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Her had to. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Your mother was at home washing so she could look after you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh ye
s. And she used to be up in the mornings when we worked in pit in't winter drying our drawers in front of fire you know, pit drawers - the were all there airing - as a young, and you would have to miss putting iron on at weekend when they'd gone out to cl
ear round - then we'd have none on. (Irons on clogs he means)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 On your clogs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 On clogs, oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did your father repair clogs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No. No. Me mother repair - aye me mother clogged 'em. Aye. She was the clog women.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did she make your cloths too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Oh no, no, she didn't make our clothes but - we got a suit every - Jubilee. Every Preston Guild. Aye. What - (Preston Guild) - local holiday. (not literal i.e. once in a blue-moon)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Were they always new or did you have to have them secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 I'd plenty that way. Same here new with me being -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Secondhand you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Now with me being tall here there's plenty passed away and left. And that's the truth. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9664688\charrsid3812201 And I'm just the right size for the ordinary man.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 So you still - have seconds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh I don't care. Oh yes, I'm just the right size for ordinary man, not to be - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 How many rooms did you have in the house in Manchester Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 We'd 4. It was a very big house, very big house and three and four a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did just the family live there or any relatives or lodgers with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No. No, no, no just the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 And your mother wouldn't have any help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 And she did her own washing of course?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well - and somebody else and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You say your mother did all the repairing of clogs but she didn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12282517\charrsid3812201 sew}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  clothes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye, did. Aye, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did your father do anything in the house, did he help your mother at all with the family work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 I couldn't say he did - I couldn't say that he did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did he never bath you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Or read you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 We'd no bath. We had to go baths if we could }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12282517\charrsid3812201 find t\rquote coppers.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Where did you bath then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh - well I go - well we used to have a big tin and bath in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 How many times, once a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Once. Aye. You see, when we come home from pit -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 As a child how often would you have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well - it weren't very week, we had it every fortnight. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 How often did you change clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You change - you change to the same suit. You'd no other. You'd no other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What about underwear, you'd have to change those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well - I didn't wear no underwear then, it - they were three quarter - they were full lined pants them days, full lined.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 So you'd just wear your suit and your shirt and nothing else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9664688\charrsid3812201 
Ayes, aye, you - the whatsisname shirt and then I were lucky if I had one for Sunday, cover it up and one of them collars that you could just wipe ever and wipe you know. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 It weren't p
lastic, I - well not cardboard but they used to - used to have a lot them days, you could put it on, fasten your stud through and a bit of a tie through it and wipe it ever with a cloth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You wouldn't wear that as a boy?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well - oh no, when I were dressed up. Oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What about when you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 How often would you change your shirt then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well - we'd nothing to change I tell you. We were lucky if we had a change.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 So your mother had to wash them while you were in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Many a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Then put them on the next day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
That's right. You see, in them days there was too many pits where we lived. There was ten in two miles and that's what made 'em slack. Means they couldn't work full time, you know. If there'd }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 been less}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
 pits, they'd have supplied the coal and we'd have been on full time but with being too many pits they couldn't sell it, couldn't sell it. I liked in t'pit, oh I like if you could get the money, you know. But we couldn't. The time kill
ed it we didn't always work three days you know, you'd go three times - time we'd have to come out - no railway trucks. Nothing to put it in so we had to come out - we'd not done full three days come times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 This would be before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Yes. Yes, b
efore - oh aye, when 191 war was on we had to work full time unless you got a doctor's note. And we didn't get no big wages and then another thing as happed in the '14 war, there were that many colliers went, they were short, and I was twenty-six, so befo
re we could be shouted in t'street with women who's husbands and sons had gone they give us star badges to show as we were starred men you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 So they wouldn't give you the white feather you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 That's it. Well in close to our house there were
 pit winding water twenty-four hours a - the clock round. Well then the winders, fire-beaters and coal, they'd never want it. Me and two brothers filled it up in spare time to save them six men working, they'd find something else to do and save the coal a
nd we filled it up in - when we'd done at night in the pit in spare time. No - no bone holders, not them days you know. We had use - we had use a tub and a kittler.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 When you first started work what time did you start in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Six o'clock.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What time did you finish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well two o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 And you got how much a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well one then - one and ten a day. One and ten a day that's what we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you have holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You never did. You - you were in debt for twelve months }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 after}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  - you'd had a few holidays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you think it was a fair wage for the time though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Was it thumpers a fair wage. Well you can reckon it up yourself, I mean, a penny were a penny but we hadn't a penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 When you were on full time did you work Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh when t'war was on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 But before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No. No. No, no, no, only when war was on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 How do you think your employer treated you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Bad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Tell me about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well, I'll tell you. Now listen, when I went in p
its and I told you at 13 I was on what was flat rate, that's what the master pays you and you got little rises when you 6 months - and six months - but they weren't - they weren't so good, you follow me? Now you see, I went with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 a set}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  of men, that's what t
hey call colliers - they join - Now the - listen! this is where the trouble starts. We'd so much a ton for our coal, so much a ton for doing our roof. You follow me? Right! Now every ton of coal we fill we had to fill 21 hundred weight to the ton. Now the
n
 we build our roof. We had to build a roof for the road to go under, pack it - and we had to pay for our own caps and our own powder as we blow 'em with. Oh. Aye, it's the shot we had to make up - blow our own holes and there'd be a shot maker and he'd bl
ow it and then we had to dress it up and pack it, each side you know, and we paid for our own cap and powder 'cos it were used to blow it. We paid for that. And we paid 6d. a week for our oil as burnt in our lamps - if we worked one day!
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Who did you pay it to, the pit owner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye, if were knocked of. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 Yes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 , they were wicked days, wicked. I - and then in the winter - two schoolteachers lived a bit higher up. Frosty. "Will you - is the boys in?" Our coals come, would you tell them?" Big thumping mound
 of coal tipped at bottom of drive, em and me other brother as is gone and we wheeled it up and packed it in his shed and we've done it was going dark - sixpence apiece, and a jam butty and then we go night after sweeping up, and we got a jam butty apiece
, and glad of it. We did. Oh had hard days. Aye. they were wicked. You see - you see, if you liked you couldn't get the money you see, the job in the pit it were all right but you couldn't get money. No, you couldn't get it, the time killed you }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 ,you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  see, the time killed you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 How did you get on with the rest of the people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Well they were all right. I mean the biggest enemies in pit you know, if they was biggest enemies and they were in trouble they helped one another. It doesn't matter if they're biggest enemy in world, if he's in trouble they'll help one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 They were comrades?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh yes, on betting, oh yes they do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Would you have liked to do another job or did you like the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 I liked it, it were - it were time that did it you see, the time as we worked. It were all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you have to serve an apprenticeship for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well, no, you serving it when you're going - as your going on you see. As - as you're moving up in age and you - you're learning
 as you're going on you see. We knowed everything only - we knowed when there was gas. You know when there gas and it always makes for the roof, we know that but the bosses like they've gone through all that source, we know what had to be done when there 
were gas in the place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What had to be done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Well that cuts - screens to turn the air out, to drive it you see. It happen come in the workings and they put screens up and drive it away, off, up the other air road you see. But they know all them th
ings beside as we didn't know, like - you know, but we know how to - how to work a seam of coal, we'd served out time to it you see, where some of the bosses had passed on papers on all the gas but they'd no idea how to work a seam of coal. No, they hadn'
t.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 And in 1911 you were filling the tubs and pulling it away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Drawing. What we call drawing. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Were you in a union in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Union? Yes. And I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 In 1911?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Yes. And I'll tell you what else we had to do, I didn't 
tell you this but I will tell you. We had a - a man as - what they call a check weight man used to be in office, as the tubs come up the pit, master's man and our man and they had - they used to weigh them and book them and our man see as they were writte
n - they got the correct weight and tubs, over again the master's man. And then we had to pay for - have a pit sharpener to sharpener our picks, we had to pay him. - Colliers!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 So you wouldn't bring much home would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well that's what we had to do I tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What happened when you brought it home, did you give it all to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
I did. Me father knew what we got because - he worked in pit you see. But then used to get a penny in the shilling. Sometime I've had sevenpence and sometime sixpence, spending money. That's all. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 When you were down the pit did you feel that there was a division of interest amongst the workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well, no, I don't think there were. There were - there were better men than others you know, for wo
rking. You see, I'll tell you another thing as they did. You see, all these places - they called 'em places - there might be two, three or four in a set, they got their own pay - wage ticket and you had to divide, you know, when it came - when you got it 
Friday you got a - the man in - as named the place got the lot and he divided it. I'll tell you another dirty trick they used to do, the masters. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 
We might have a good place here, we've got the coal moving, it's a good place. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Now all -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You mean a good place to dig in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye, the coal - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 nicer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  - the nicer seam than what some are, you see there must weight on coal to make 'em nice, softer, you follow me? Now - we'll say another place lower down - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 
there\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  wasn't so good - and they'd fetch one of thei
r men out of there and put him in our place and one of ours would go up there - and our wage as - this wage as he got in our place helped his set out and that man as went in his place lowered ours - so as they wouldn't have to pay the minimum wage. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 Now they did all them dirty tricks. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
You see - they were all in one ridge and we were in another and they had to get it and pool it - you see!
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 So the wages was more or less pooled?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Ayes, that's right and it shouldn't have been because if you're on mini
mum, what they call minimum, you were t'min. you couldn't help it. If you were on piece and doing all right they should have left you be. But no, they - lower yours to make theirs more even lower so as they wouldn't have to give them anything. Oh they did
 all the dirty tricks yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you think there was a big difference between trained craftsmen and other workers when you were in the pit, before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well you see, they never called ours a trade. They never called ours a trade, a collier. But in
 - in a sense it was, because you could take strongest man in world or strongest two men and sent him on a coal face, he'd have no idea how to make it go. So a fellow as is learnt from a boy would know better than him, or those two, wouldn't he. That's so
 that is. I - I've worked - I've had Irish men - good men with a spade but they were as numb as that and they never cut a thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You know the men who actually got the coal - the colliers - and the men who moved it in tubs, there'd be a difference betwe
en the two wouldn't there, in the wages and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Well it's the same as I tell you I started just on fourteen. You'd two men, I were what we call a drawer, that - how - bringing it up the face to the place where it was sent off to the pit you see. 
Well as I got older it kept rising. We had four shillings, they got eight. When I were fourteen that were good. And they got eight. Now as I went older I come to five shillings, to make, they call that a coalmate and then as I got to eighteen, six - six e
i
ghts to a mate. Right, now when I'm nineteen, I've seven to a mate but with being a good lad, not swanking on this road and used to the road they give me same as them. They put me as a share same as them but I've been working for a firm, they would not gi
ve me the full }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 rate}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
 'til I were twenty-one. But they give me a share because I worked for them. And if a tub weren't filled, used to go and fill it. Out you go and put and put em empty. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you think there was a division between trained craftsmen and labourers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Yes. There - they weren't - they weren't quite as bad as they are today because I mean to say if you did - did - if you unscrewed that screw there and it weren't your job - they're on strike aren't they. You shouldn't have done tha
t, it were his job, they're on strike today aren't they.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What was the difference otherwise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well they - they worked more together than what they do today, a tradesman and a - the labourer. They worked more together, my opinion.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you think that the tradesman had a better standard of living than the labourer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well they had much - they had a bit more but not a - not a great lot, not a great lot, no, no. Hadn't a great lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 When you started work did you think it changed your attitude to life in general?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Aye, well - well I - I've seen in me time in the summer months and I'm not telling a word of a lie, I've seen forty to fifty men, sixteen to fifty odd stood at corner of street and we hadn't a penny in our hands and we couldn't help it. Couldn't help it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 So you did see a lot of poverty as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Yes, yes. I ran two mile for a jam butty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What would you have for breakfast if you were very poor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What did we have? Well I'll tell God's truth, I've never told nobody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Do you mind telling me?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
I don't. You'll not believe it if I tell you, we had - bread with some hot water and sugar. That was me breakfast. I remember that. Not milk on. Hot water on bread and sugar. That's what -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What would you have for your dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Well - I were hungry many a time. Well sometimes mother'd make a potato pie. Or - but - it didn't go far enough when there were - when there was four hungry bellies waiting for it, ayes, and sometimes we had - she made a potato pie 
or - anything - potatoes and a bit of meat on or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 How often would you have meat in a week do you think as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 We didn't get much, no, we didn't. No. No. Well this backache now as I've got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You're seventy-nine?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
On Monday. And a lot I don't know. That's what happens when you've been in pit. You get stuff - flack - what they call blows, coal flies out, hits you in th'eye or in face and you just rub it and it's sore you never bother. Eventually it's affecting your
 eye, you know, and years later it comes on and that's what you used to get.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 How did you like school as a boy? We were doing your meals weren't we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What did you have for tea, you had hot-pot when your mother could manage meat for dinne
r, otherwise you had potatoes you were telling me, what about tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Well, more often than not I had scrambled outside anywhere where I could get it more teatimes than teas. That's right. Errand here or going there or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Doing jobs you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Anything - any little jobs, yes, yes. I've done all sorts of jobs. I helped undertaker, I've helped carry many a boy you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 As a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well - a young man, I've helped carry 'em you know, no hearse. And I have - and we had to keep chang
ing over and I've had black shoulders because of carrying and we'd no tea when we got home, they couldn't afford it. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You mean you helped poor people take the corpse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Yes, many a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Tell me about the funerals that you've been to, the very poor people couldn't afford a hearse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No. No, no, no. Well it was a good mile I should think from the church, Peel church, Little Holton, St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 Paul\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  Peel and we lived at top end of Little Holton. Well, if you had a dec}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 
ent suit - they wanted a carrier}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
. Send down, if you hadn't and they wanted a carrier, you might be able to borrow one of somebody's, they swopped in bury you know, suits and I think many a time - and it was kept changing over you know, the - the things they carried them on then t
hey don't do now, that were very heavy. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 Have you seen them? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Well we carried and carried and changing over and changing over and we used to be tired. I've had black }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 shoulders}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
 with carrying and then we couldn't have no tea. You've gone home. Yes. Aye, I've had that many a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Do you remember a funeral in your family?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 I remember me brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 How old would you be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Fifteen - half a minute - fifteen - I'd be turned twenty - oh my other brother died at home, my oldest brother died at h
ome. In 42 he died. The oldest brother, I'm th'oldest now. And he died at home. Me father died. Then me mother, mother lived to ninety-two. A grand woman, tall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 And yet she was underfed and overworked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye. Gangrene come in her leg.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 At your brother's funeral when you were young before 1918, who went and what sort of clothes did they wear, do you remember?}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well we were lucky, I'll tell you why. We were lucky he were working at death. And we had - we hadn't a Scotsman as a rule but there
 were one used to be in village, and father went to this Scotswoman wanting suits. We went to be measured and they were ready. Pending compensation. They were blue suit like this, only that was best suit we'd had for a while. Then we lent it many a time t
o people, funerals you know, just for funeral and that's how we come to get a good suit and we got forty pound for him, that's all, over funeral because of father living, he weren't - we weren't dependant on him, that's all we got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Just enough for the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well no, it'd be - they wasn't so much them days but because we'd a father - he'd a father living we weren't called dependant }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 on}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  him you see and he got forty pound.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 And you came back to tea did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well we had a bit then at home,
 oh aye. Now when me brother died, he were in a poor way. Me niece come, one of his daughters, comes here and - he'd four - he'd three girls. One, youngest, were only eighteen months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Was this before 1918 too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No. No-no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 What time did you have to go to bed when you were a child, did you have to at any special time?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No. No, no, no. We weren't - we didn't go - stop up late but we'd no special time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you have jobs to do in the house when you were a boy to help your mother? Or to help your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
No, my works outside, whenever I could get anything. Outside anywhere, any errand, anything, I've took - I've carried homing pigeons Walkden Stocks, used to send them away, me and me brother. Right - a mile and a - two
 mile, big basket, carry them. Anything we - as we could lay our hands on to do we did it. Up at five o'clock blackberrying in the - in the clough and they were all black and schoolteacher and give us sixpence for a quart or some red'uns in fourpence. Too
 many red'uns in she didn't want 'em. Aye. So we had them. Blackberry pies and blackberry dumplings, jolly good too. They don't know they've been born.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you share a bedroom or a bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No, no, we had to have four in one room, very big room. Four in one room. No more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Four boys in one room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 How many sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 I've two and they're both living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 How many children did your mother have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 About six altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 How many boys and how many girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well there were two girls and - four boys. I've two brothers living, one's - one was twice as old as the other -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 This youngest was the only one out of the family not allowed down the pit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 That's right, mother wouldn't let him go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 She was so upset about the other one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye, and he's sixty-five and he's gone living at Bradford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 So both your sisters are spinsters, they never married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Yes, and I lived with them. I were on ration - me food.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 But did you get on all right as children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Oh yes, oh yes, but they followed the old style like when they were young and the rationed me food, you follow me? I were half clemmed to death till I come here. And me bit of spending money, I used to spend it on food you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 When you were a child was there anyone you were particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Well - I don't know, only this old chap and old woman who had this shop and I never were there, I didn't sleep there because I were always having something to eat off 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You were close to them because you got food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye. Oh aye. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Where did you have your meals as a family as a boy in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh yes. In the kitchen - in the - aye in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Where did your mum cook and what did she cook on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 We had a - we had a back kitchen like you know, where she cooked. Oh she'd gas. Aye, she'd gas, aye. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What time did you have breakfast and did you all have it together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well you see, when we did work we were off, you know, catch as catch can, get out to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What about when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Well, no, you - you weren't all home at same time, just depending what speed you come on, it were above a mile to school, you had to hop skip and jump back and go same - you know - no 
ride no nothing. Rain or snow. No - you'd come back then hop back at dinnertime then back - then at teatime. Well you can just catch what were - what was put on the table. Oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 So you wouldn't all have breakfast together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Father would probably have it first you mean?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 And then the workers would come as they grew up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did your mother make her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Yes. Yes. And flour cakes and - in the lobby cooling aye and we could murder one with some butter on. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did she make jam or pickles or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No, she didn't make jam, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did she make any wine or beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you grow your own vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No. No, we'd no - we'd no garden, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you ever eat tinned meat as a boy, how many times a week do you think you'd have meat as a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 I'm just studying, I've no memories of meat as a boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you ever have tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Do you ever remember your mother having less food so that you children could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Yes. Yes. Me father - in particular. When he worked in pit he'd come home and we weren't working then and he'd sit our - potato pie, we'd sit round table. And he's give us some and he could have eat
en all lot himself. He give us - he give us some and he could eat lot - I've seen him, I have, and then at Sunday when we were having our tea all together, a sandwich cake. Aye. Aye. We're looking, looking, which is biggest piece. We were taking one and w
e were waiting biggest piece come. Aye. Aye. Aye. Oh yes. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 I don't have to ask if you had to clean your pate because obviously you did didn't you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Think we did. We }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1051900\charrsid3812201 licked}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  it - we licked it if there were nobody looking. Licked it. Never mind a \{ILLEGIBLE\} and forth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Were you allowed to talk at the table or were they very strict with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Very strict. Very strict, very strict.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Could you leave when you wanted or did you have to ask?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No, we could leave when you'd done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Could you bring a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
No, no. Now listen, we'd say - we had a dresser, a lovely dresser, me mother and father had it when they were married and - a dresser, they were a bonny thing - and us going to touching that were like going to a f
ire. We were teached from children it were like going to fire and that dresser, me sister has it today and it's nicer than what it - when - when it were bought, when mother married. And you daresn't go and - oh you'd get shot it you come like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 She was so proud of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Well it only - only teaching wasn't it - it'd do no harm to us, it was just wood, if we were only touching fire. Now in this small room where we are - listen to this, where we go in the small room -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Were your mother and father very strict with you as children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 In - in the house, yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you have to hold your knife and for, in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Knife and fork? We had no knife and fork. We had no knife and fork.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What did you use, a spoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you have your own seats round the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Oh aye, we had our own places, oh yes. No we had no knife and fork. Father used to have a basin for his tea to drink his tea out of a basin. Aye, not a cup, not a cup and saucer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What did you children have?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 A - a pint pot. A big pot you know, you could keep your hands on, not cups. No cups, oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Do you remember your younger brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Where were they fed until they were old enough to come to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Well, no, me mother - did what her could do and they used to get buttermilk. It were only threeha'pence - were it threeha'pence a gallon - threeha'pence a quart. Threeha'pence a quart, buttermilk. Used to buy that mother and that were cheap enoug
h weren't it. I don't know what it is now. I never see none now. Her pulled through best road her could to feed us and as we grew up and then we had to scrap a bit outside for what we could get and we used get.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Where did the babies sit before they were old enough to come to the table, do you remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Well they - they'd sit in a - in a - easy chair - a chair you know. They weren't all really steps, there were years in between them all you see. There was years, and there was one we would - we
 were coming up like would take our place you see. There were years between 'em, I tell you there were twelve years between them two as I told you, twelve years and then you see this oldest sister now, she's seventy-four and t'others knocking at door for 
seventy, they live in their own house and they're living - they - they both have their pension in their own right. You see. There's like a gap between them all practically. And I remember this brother - sixty-five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 I wasn't there 
to - there were only me in house with me mother and him in bed, and he - something went wrong with him or something. Go and tell your father. Well he were out front and I remember telling him, mother wants you. I remember it as plain as it were today.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Who helped your mother,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1051900\charrsid3812201  did}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  she have a nurse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
No, no, no, not they, there were an old woman used go - no, come and help wash for two or three days and then bob's your uncle, help one another. Oh she never went away had no nurse. Oh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 She didn't even have a midwife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
No, no, an old woman as used - no, no. No, you see, I can see old woman now coming in th'ouse. Aye, I can. They'd help wash her baby things happen for a day or two then - that were the lot. Oh no, no nurse.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you have a lot of friends near where you lived when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Oh yes, yes, I had plenty of friends actually - at me sister's now you see. I went - I left - mind you, I don't really blame me sisters for -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 When you were a boy did people come, were they 
asked to have a drink, did you have visitors a visit and come for a meal or a drink or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Never bothered about a drink. Never bothered that to ask you have a drink. No they didn't bother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 When you were a boy and you had friends come they were never given a drink, did you visit friends and did they visit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you visit relatives or did they visit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well I'll tell you I were going a cadging if I went. You know what cadging is? A jam butty at grandmother's, mile and a half down road.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 She lived a mile and a half away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did neighbours come in and out of your house though, you say they came in to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye. When - when they had a baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 That was all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye, or you were - anybody - 
if she's not so well they'd come and help - they help one another, no nurses coming. And we - we're in a good home here aren't we. You know what they did in my days if they had no home? Workhouse. And do you know what they used - they used to let him out 
a day a week or half a day and they'd all white coat and pants on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 White cord pants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You could tell anybody as come from workhouse. He'd white cord pants on in my day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What workhouse would this be - Atherton Workhouse or the Bolton one?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 Townsley}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 Where Townsley hospital is now there's the big, what we call the workhouse t'other side. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 That's where they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you ever know anybody in the workhouse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 I did. Yes. I knowed one or two from down our way. I did, I did, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 They were too poor in their old age to manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye, and - and their relations didn't want 'em, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 But you remember them from the workhouse as a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 I do that, yes, I do, yes. I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 She was very grand woman and her was straight. Straight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Was she able to show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Her was tall - very tall and smart.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 And affectionate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Yes. Her were ninety-two when she died and she was sensible up to ninety-one. And we
 had a little bit of money and she shared it all fair, you know, I mean all between us, aye, all worked at once, she shared it all fair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 When you were a boy could you take your troubles to your mother if you were upset?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye, aye, aye, so and so's been hitting me. Well, hit him back, you know. Aye, that's what she said.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What about your dad, was he easy to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 He was very straight - very straight, had to be careful - what we said. What you said, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Was he affectionate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye. Oh aye, and no messing. What he said were law you know. What he said, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Was he affectionate with you though?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You could share your worries with him could you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye, aye. He got a nice job after his pit days. Y
ou see, I told you they have a - they used to have a man come out of pit to check - what they call check weighing for-men, over again the master's man. He got that. That's on the top, bubs come up pit, check whose it was and the weight over again the mast
er's man. Well he got that job, he were on the top then, not down and they took a vote all through pit for that who got it at last two and he got it. That were in his later years when he - you know - getting finishing days really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What do you think your dad and mother hoped you would grow up to be and what did they teach you was most important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Well - we just existed. Scores, hundreds beside me with just - they'd now look forward to. They'd nothing to look forward to, only best road we'd make our own way anyway we could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What do you think they thought was important in life, what rules did they make for you children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well they'd never no chance of any - any - progress in moving anywhere because we hadn't won scholarship, I hadn't 
you see when I went to school. It was only eighteen the girl as we call teaching us. She was only seventeen or eighteen, wasn't a proper teacher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What kind of a school did you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 Paul\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  Peel, Little Holton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 It was a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Church - church -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Was it boys and girls mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Yes, church school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 How old were you when you first started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well I went before I were five and I went 'til I was - half time twelve and then I finished at thirteen. Well you see I we
re always tall, I remember it same as it were today, and I were always very good at reckoning up, you see, always very good but I never were good at reading. Never good at spelling. And I remember the fault, I was in the second class, not the first, and w
i
th being tall they were short in the standard one and they moved me from the second class, kicked the first class and went in standard one. And I missed that, I didn't get that clear, you follow me. I missed a standard and I missed the - missed of the - b
eing able to spell properly you see. But I always good at reckoning sums - always. They used to come like and - happen - quarter past three, shut at four you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you go the full day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Yes. And - and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You went home for your dinner, you didn't have school dinners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You went on your own did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Hop skip and run didn't matter whether it snowed, same back. Same back. So I tell you - about three o'clock sum day - sums and give you sum. First hand up cut when you give it.
 It was generally first out. You know, give you a sum, I were out first often than not. And it went in rotation like you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you like school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh I were all right. Oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 How did you like the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well I tell you it were - but she wasn't a full qualified teacher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 But you'd have more than one wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Well you went up the same as I tell you with missing this standard, this class it knocked me back you see in me spelling, knocked me - I can tell you it was that
 was did it because I were good on reckoning up and sums, there were nobody better than me on reckoning up and sums you know but I slacked - I slacked in the spelling, you follow me? Slacked in the spelling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What did you think of the other teachers, the teachers as a whole, did you like them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Oh well they were - they were very good, they were - head master and then assistant headmaster, they were very good but that's where I slipped up and I've tumbled to it myself to how I slipped up not being a good reader.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 Do you remember things they emphasised as important in life, things like good manners or tidiness or ways of speaking?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well they never said much about that but I'll tell you what they - I remember it as if it was - fetch some pape
rs round - signing for the pledge, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 In the day school they did this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye, well what did we know about booze that's right, what did we know about it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What happened, what did they tell you about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well you - they give me
 a paper and they told you like would you sign tee - to be teetotal, never drink and - all. Well we - we knew nothing about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 It's usually in church they ask you about the temperance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No, that were in - that - that - that were in school, oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did they read you lectures on it though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Yes, yes, in - in school, yes, they did, oh yes. Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 If you did something the teachers didn't like what happened, how did they punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did they punish girls as well as boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Cane, yes, on the hand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What did they punish you for usually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 If we done something you shouldn't do, you know, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well you'd been talking when somebody - she's been talking, shut up and you - you don't stop. Come out. Then you shift your hand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did your mum and dad go to school, were they interested in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh yes, oh they went to school. Was nothing com - no pit books, nothing to take home you know, we don't want to finish at s
chool, no - no school books to come home with. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did your mum and dad go to school to see the teachers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well aye, aye, they went there many a time. Oh yes, but - everything went pretty fair at school, you couldn't grumble like on the - th
em poor days, they were poor days you know and they couldn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Were the other children from the same types of home as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Practically. Practically round there, practically. All - all come from the village, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did the teachers treat them all the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh yes, oh yes, they were all treated same, all the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Do you ever remember anyone left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No, we didn't - we didn't show any preference one or another, you know, they just carried on their usual - one were as }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 good}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  as the other, oh no, was all -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you have gangs or groups in your school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Never were any gangs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 And you always went to the same school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh yes, I went to the same school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you go to evening school at all afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No. No. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 
We'd get no books nor nothing to take home for any lessons, no we finished when - when day school was finished.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What did you feel about your education, did you think it was worthwhile?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well when I co
me to reckon up the same as I've just told you, through missing that it knocked me back for a sixer through missing that class, with not being a good reader.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Do you think you benefited though from your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well I - I must have benefited a bit mustn't I but - through missing that I think that knocked me back you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 When you left school did you still live at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh yes, yes. Aye. I slept at this while this old fellow who had the shop across the road had two parts of our food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 When you left school did you change your ways of living, did you still go to church and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Not so often. No, I were out scrounging, you know what scrounging is? I had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you have new friends, did you change your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
No, no, same, we all - we used to go out what we could get anywhere helping or doing a bit of a job or anything we could get, we could earn a copper we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you go dancing or playing any kinds of games when you were in your teens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No, no I didn't go dancing, yes, yes, when I got older I went to - learn to roller skate and then I played at whist. Whist drive. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 And you went out with your friends boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh I mixed up then. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did your parents like you to bring your friends home and did you have to be in at a certain time in your teens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No, never brought no friends home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 I don't know but we didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You've never been married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Married - no, no. No I've never been married, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 And you've always lived in Bolton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye. So I didn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did your father like a drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
No. He would when he were young but he went teetotal. He went teetotal. No. No, he didn't a - and me mother - big church woman. Aye. So - I used to go wh
en she were - not good, then I'd take her a little bottle of milk stout. You know what used to say to me sister, I could sup a quart of anybody's brew and when there were in bed they used to give her half a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 egg cupful}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 .
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did your mother go out on her own when you were younger, did she have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Oh ayes, went to - if we'd concerts at school or anything like that she were there. Oh yes. In the mothers union, oh yes, she were in that. Aye, yes, oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did your father go out a lot when you were young, did he go to clubs or pubs or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 He went to pubs when he were young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did your mum go with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No. No. No, her didn't drink in a sense. Not like it is today you know, they generally go together don't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 But your mum and dad didn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 And they go into a club or went into a pub they generally link together don't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did your father take an interest in sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 He - yes, I'll tell you, he could tell you all the horses - 
these racehorses - what they were bred of, what they'd won, all their career and all the rest of it. He could give you all that, he had it down in black and white in his books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did he bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 He did bet a bit but he did all this, he said, he were on his deathbed and me sisters come in, they, we'd sixpence a piece on big winner.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 He said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 They said, you see. He said, well it's all right. But there's now in it. There's now in it. Aye, there's now in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did he go to races when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 He did, yes, he did. I went - I've been once that's all in my life, I went to Manchester, the only time - Manchester.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Were your mother and father in any sick clubs or funeral clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Yes, of course we were, we all were. Penny clubs 
as they call them you entered when you were a baby didn't you. Yes. Entered when you were a baby. Then if you - if you want a rise as you get older you pay another copper. Now take me now -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 As a child was your mother in any boot clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Boot club
s? There were - no, she didn't but I - but there was a lady or two did in the village, you know, pay so much and - like - they're going now. They pay so much a week don't you and then when you pay so - aye, aye, that - there were a lady did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You were actually in the Bolton borough weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You were really between Tyldesley, Atherton and Bolton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 It was actually in Bolton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 When your mum and dad weren't doing their work how did they spend their spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Well - I can tell you some history of me father. We had a coalman and he did me father - he was doing me father a good turn. He'd two fields and he were - ploughing 'em. And he's given me father good turn, he's finding him a job hay m
aking. Do him a good turn. There all day, then he finishes at night, got three shilling at night, and not being used to a rake, you have to be - it's a nack you know using a rake, his hands were all blistered to top. Yes. And he said, there's no more haym
aking, cows can get their own in. Chap had done him a good turn, this coalman, through helping him but he had - I can see his hands with blisters on now. He give him three shilling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 When they weren't working how did they spend their spare time though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well - father hanged about anywhere same as us, we're stood at corner of street having meetings and chatting and that's all they could do.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Your dad didn't go to political meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Wasn't he interested in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 W
ell no, not much. Oh he got on stores committee. On the Co-op committee and they came on the pictures committee. They had - they - they showed them at the co-op hall and he was on that committee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 But he wasn't interested in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No, he never bothered much with that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did he never vote even?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 He voted, oh aye, he voted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 He never talked about politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Not much, no. No. Father I know he used to be a Liberal. And then he changed over to Labour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Why was he Liberal, did he ever say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Well they were good people in them days and they did fair. Lloyd George, I think he were one of the best leaders we ever had in this country for the state. Lloyd George. Not a warmonger but for the state, for the country. I think he were 
one of best Prime Ministers we ever had, Lloyd George, dead and gone he is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Were you interested in politics as you grew up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Yes, yes. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did your mother eve vote, was she interested in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh aye, aye, aye, oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did she vote the same as your dad or did she have her own views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Her had her own views. But they'd be same I think then. Well you see, in them days Liberals got in as many times as Conservatives practically. And you see there were Liberals wen
t in as many times as nearly as many as Conservatives them days. Because there was no Labour, you see. Nearly gone now these Liberals aren't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Why did your father change to Labour, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well - we had a - I went to the meeting and we 
had a Liberal there and he were - he were Member of Parliament and he said, he'd stand down when they ever got a good - better man. And there were Tom }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 Greenhaulgh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  was a miner's agent, Tom-reenhaulgh and he was putting up and he said he'd sta}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 nd down for him and Tom Greenhaul}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
gh got it. He got in. He got in. I remember Tom Greenaulgh saying at this meeting, it's true, now, he says, I've got a shilling an hour eight hours a day, he got a shilling an hour eight hours a day, I can remember that. A shilling an hou
r eight hours a day, that were guaranteed. But it were only three days a week. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 When you were a child did you go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Tell me about your Sunday school days? You were Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh yes. Well - we used to e
njoy it, it were all right, it killed a good hour you know. There was nowhere to else to go. We didn't go every time you know because me and another fellow used to have a walk and we'd been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 When you were a boy did you go every week though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No, I'm just telling you, we used to have a walk, we'd been and we hadn't. Daresn't let me mother know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did she and your father go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No, they - father didn't go much. Me mother did. Mother went every Sunday. Every Sunday night. Tall woman, 
big tall woman, smart too. Aye, went every Sunday night. Her did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You just went to Sunday school, not to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Odd times, but - no I didn't - half a minute - sometimes - no, I didn't go to Sunday school. We went to church, we didn't go Sunday 
school went to church when we went. The day school in daytime then it were church at Sunday, not the church - not school church - class, no, it were - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you go on any cuttings with the church when you were a boy and where did you go and what did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Never had none with 'em. No. Never had none. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you belong to the choir or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No, I never - no, I weren't in choir. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you say grace at your house at meals?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Unless you said it under your breath. You had to say it under your breath if you did, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you say prayers at night though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No. Never said that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You were a wicked thing weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 We weren't. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you ever take part in any social activities at church when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No, we took no part.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you have different clothes to go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did I thump. I managed to get a pair of shoes one time and I went in them, I walked in procession with m
e clogs on and many a lot beside me, because had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 no}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You never had to go barefoot though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No, I never went barefoot, no. I'd no -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 It was mostly clogs and shoes for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye, well I - it were clogs often than not we all wear. Clogs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Were you allowed to play games on Sunday or did your people think it was wrong to work and play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well - no, we never played games much, we - we used to play football other nights - with a rag ball, made rag ball you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 How did you make it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh tied it up with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1051900\charrsid3812201 string}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  and - and put - and turn it back. Oh I'll tell you what we used to do. There were a Mr Topp, the mill owner, living in a big house. We'd have a meeting. Some - of the lads. We'd go to Mr Topp, he had - he liv
ed in a big house and we'd have a meeting, ay, let's have a letter written, best writing lad, would write a letter begging for money for a ball. We go ring the bell and say we've come - will you give that Mr Topp? And we stood there, with our hats off. Re
member it very well - eeh, he says, it not long since I gave you sixpence for a ball. Yes, but it's bust - it's busted Mr Topp. You know, thank you, we all thanked him.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 And you got sixpence?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 For a ball.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you buy a ball with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh aye, aye, there was two of us, the two of us. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 
Aye, we had to buy a ball. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye, he were - he were grand fellow. And all there's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 built}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  on now where his big house was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 It's been pulled down and built on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 When you were a boy what did you do with your Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Saturdays? Well I used to sneak up to golf links. Byron's golf links, that was at back of Bradley pits and try to get a job caddying. Caddying yes, and find any balls - get tuppence or threepence for one if I found one. Well 
eventually I got me own man to carry when he come, he were my man when he come out. Everytime when he come. And we got threepence a round and when we finished a jam butty and a drink of tea if you wanted tea. And when you're getting - professional golfers
 
looked after the links, he fixed this out what you had to have and when you'd been there a while and he thought you were giving sticks out right to suit him you know without asking for it he'd make you a first class caddy then he'd give you fourpence a ro
und and then you had your drink of tea and a jam butty when you'd done. But we made more money finding balls. We went along our travels you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What other jobs did you do while you were at school, you were a caddy, did you say you made black puddings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye - I fetched the blood form the - from half a mile down the road. You used blood you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 How did you bring it? Not in a wheelbarrow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No, I had two - two big tins with lids - with lids on and I - I had a trindle and we'd stop and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What's a trindle?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
What you bowl with. What do you call them. Aye, we call them trindles. You see, if that glass wasn't in there, no handle, that's be a trindle wouldn't it. Have you never seen children playing with a trindle. Well they call them
 trindles. Well I'd put that and get in between it and put these things one at each side to stop them from splashing me, and they would hold me - hold 'em out when I were walking, see. Hold them out as I was walking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Sort of hook that they play bowl and hoop with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
That's right. Well it must have been a mile away and we used - and I used to take it up, it must have been a mile away. We had used to carry it from the butchers to this fellow, old fellow. Must have been a mile away. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 So the butcher didn't make the black puddings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
No, no, we got the blood from there and this old fellow come - made 'em and I were learning and helping, same with tripe. He did it. I helped - mile away from the butchers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 How did you make them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Make black puddings? Well I'll tell you how they start off. You put your groats in a bag in a boiler, tie it up. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 Then you cut your leaflard up, it should be leaflard in little blocks, follow me. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Now then, you get your skins and you clean - wash 'em and you 
cut 'em in lengths, tie one end up and put 'em over a tin ready for the job. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 
Now then, when you've done with your groats boiled you put 'em in a big mug, put some blood in and then you mix them with sage, thyme and salt and then you start with a tun dish. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
You put your skin on a tun dish, fill it up, piece of skin - piece of fat, many fats as you want then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Put blood in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh bloods mixed amongst, in - in - in the big whats name, mug, it's mixed there and then you tie, you - you fill it up and twis
t it round and tie the end up. Then when you've done what you want you put 'em in the boiler and eventually when they start boiling they start coming to top and when they start coming to top it's time to be lifting 'em out. And I've asked many a one how t
hey black }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 pudding}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
, they don't know. But I know. They're reddish when they come out of boiler. And do you know what they do? Just dip them in a drop of water and a bit of soda in, it - blacken 'em. And there's plenty doesn't know that. They don't - and that'
s how they black them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 This man had a tripe shop did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
It were a tripe and black puddings and he made meat and potato pies. They were tuppence each and mince pies. They were a penny each mince pies and I've had meat and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10970448\charrsid3812201 potato}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  pies out of th'o
ven when I've had tuppence. That where I had a lot of me food. Aye, had that, he died when I were nineteen and I could have had his business. His wife - her could serve but weren't good at much more and I could have had his business with his wife there wh
en I were nineteen, I hadn't sense. Hadn't sense you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 So you were a caddy as a boy and you made black puddings, any other jobs you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well, dressing tripe too you know like we'd - there were two, there were black puddings, and tripe. Cold
 job in winter that you know, use plenty of cold water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 I believe it's filthy when it comes isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Oh yes. Well - do you know where that oil comes for as they sell in the tripe shops neatsfoot oil. Aye, do you know where that comes from? Well
 I'll tell you. That comes off top of the boil when they put cow heels in and boil 'em. That comes out of the cow heel, skim it off the top. That's where that comes from. That's where that oil comes - that comes from.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you get paid for these jobs, when you made black puddings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Oh I've been selling them - I told them. Aye - I've been round with 'em red hot in a tin. Penny each, piece of liver cakes and mustard or salt for a penny each. I sold many a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1051900\charrsid3812201 more}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1051900\charrsid3812201 at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you buy them and then you made a profit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No. No. He give me - he give me - percentage, the old man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What did you do with that, was that your spends or did you have to give it to your mum?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Some - some of it, I didn't have it all. Didn't tell her every time, you
 know, or else you'd had nothing. Her would have had it all if you'd have told her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 She needed the money for food didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye, did, aye, we had hard time no betting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What did your parents think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh I - no, no swearing, oh no, they wouldn't let me smoke in th'house when I were twenty. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 When you were a boy if grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Never allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No. They - he were very strict in that way me father were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Who punished you if you did anything wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Well I - I'll tell you what me father done. He sent me bed and he'd send one or two - one or two of t'others bed at Sunday afternoon without tea if we done something we shouldn't have don.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Never hit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No 'til morning. And one of t'others'd fetch a bit up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Fetch a bit of food up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 On quiet. We've done that. Eeh, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Was it always your father who punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye, it weren't me mother. Mother used to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1051900\charrsid3812201 scold }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 us. (Scold)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What did you get punished for, do you remember a particular time when you were punished and how you felt about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Now what had I been doing? Oh, I'd been fighting - I'd been fighting. One fellow used go to a Wesleyan chapel and I used go down
 the road to - this Peal church and school. And we couldn't agree somehow, I don't know how it come about, we had a fight. And me mother get - me father gets here and - and bed - no tea, 'til morning. Well one of t'others fetched a bit up. I remember that
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 How did you feel about it, were you upset about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well I were a bit - having no - no tea you know, having nothing to eat. Then I had a little bit. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Who played the most important part in your life, your mother or your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh me mother. Mother, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You got most of your ideas from her, she taught you most?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 When you had a birthday what happened, was it any different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Not a difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What was Christmas Day like at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well if we got a penny, an orange or apple we were laughing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you have anything special on Christmas or a birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Orange or a apple or a penny. With a penny. You'd a good Christmas. A good Christmas. No, no
thing any more. Do you remember pace egg day, do you know what that is? Well I'll tell you. I'll tell you about that. It were pace egg day we called it and we used go to Fines, big houses, we had our map planned out we'd had years as boys, used to get egg
s
 from farm, hot across buns, pace egg, used to come back loaded. Well - Kenyon Hall then, it's built on now, Kenyon Hall, and it were private. It was private then, we daresn't go down - only at that day and we used go and we'd ring the bell and say, we've
 come. And we all got hot cross bun apiece. And we couldn't go any other day down there. Then we used to have little farm houses where we used go - go to beg. Oh we used to come back, we got a full egg that day for our breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Why was it called pa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8008749\charrsid3812201 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 e egg day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Why - I don't know why they called it but there - there is - it's called pace egg day yet but - I don't know what it represents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 So you went round to the farmers and you got an egg?
