\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well I - I - pictures were starting then, you remember pictures. They were very - you know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Jumpy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye. And we - tuppence I think it were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you get spends?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 I - I'd get coppers off people and I went in pictures.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did your mum and dad give you any pocket money though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No, no extras, oh no, oh no, no, we hadn't - no, no, you got nothing. Never got no - holidays - well there }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8008749\charrsid3812201 weren\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  as many holidays as they have and we went along. There was holiday pay, I never drawed dole in me life you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 When you were a child did you keep any pets or collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Yes. We had a - we had a dog. We had a dog. And he was very good. I'll tell you
 what he used to do. And it was a pity he had to be destroyed. We - this brother, this youngest brother now - he went to school. And this dog, we were - let's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8008749\charrsid3812201 see}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  - three minutes walk from the pit across - from the field - up the field to where we lived, t
his dog would come with us at morning and when I got near pit - stop. He'd stop there 'til we were out of sight and he'd come back. And then when it were time for this boy leaving school they'd send to school, go and fetch our Fred. He'd go and wait on pl
ayground on him coming back. It would. Yes, it would, he'd wait on him coming out of playground fetch him back. Oh he would that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you go bicycling or walking or swimming?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Bicycling - I'll tell you something about bicycling now we've gone so far. There were a little family again or house and he had a solid }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8008749\charrsid3812201 tyred}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
 bike. Solid tyre and we could borrow it for threepence for half a day, solid tyre. And sometime you got a few ha'pennies saved up and we'd get it. - Six of us. - And we'd get it sometim
e a whole day he hadn't known where we'd been but that were the 'end of it. He got no more because he couldn't. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8008749\charrsid3812201 Solid}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
 tyres. Aye - it were. Aye, no he didn't bother how many there were, that were all he got, because there were all we had, he grumbled because he knew - he couldn't get no more because there was nothing doing. Solid tyres it was, so that was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 So you never went walks or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you ever go to theatres or concerts when you were a boy at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No, not when I was a boy I couldn't. When - I went older you know I used to like going to Grand Theatre. That's closed now you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 But you didn't as a boy?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You told me when your mother was ill you had an old lady used to come in?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 When her having a baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Supposing she was ill would anybody help, neighbours or friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh aye, they're all friend - yes, they were all friends oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you have relatives who ever helped you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well - aye well that were nearest then you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Your grandmother a mile and a half a way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
People say in those days when they got together as a group they used to make their own amusement, did your parents have friends in, how would they amuse themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well, they didn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did they play games or make music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
They didn't have friends in but if there were anything going on at any of the houses they were always welcome to go. There was nobody barred, you know, if they were having a bit a filalo or anything like that they'd -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What's a filalo?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 That's a new one, there's one - one's never heard of packing sawdust in young day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What's packing sawdust?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 I told her it her, I said, that's right I can pack sawdust. She said, I've never heard of that before. 
It were right so I couldn't pack sawdust. It were never her tale weren't right I said if that's right, I could plait sawdust. They'd never heard of plait sawdust.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Before 1918 people used to divide society into different classes or groups, do you remem
ber different classes of people when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Well - yes. Where I lived there were two Miss Jardins, they were independent people, independent people. They'd speak to you as they went by, they used to have these long dresses down to their feet
 and - you know, old style. Two sisters, I remember them quite plain. And then there were Miss Topp - Mr Topp at this - they were going to church, Mr Topp from this big house and - say }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8008749\charrsid3812201 
good morning}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 .
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You'd raise your cap to him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh yes, same as 
with these two ladies. Oh yes, they'd recognize us, same coming back. Oh yes. Aye, they - we - you know, they thought they were somebody and we were - nothing apparent but - they didn't think so, the - it was us as thought like they were up in the world a
nd we were down but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Why did you think they were up and you were down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well because they were - they could dress up to nines and we couldn't. We couldn't dress up to nines, couldn't dress at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did they have different houses to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh - yes, a big house, oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 And better furniture?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Aye and bigger house - bigger house, yes. Ours one time where we lived I think it had been a mill one time and made into houses that's why ours was so big, you see, you could play footba
ll in our big room in a sense. It hold four beds in it so it must have been something - it had been a mill one time and then made into houses do you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What class would you say you and your family belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What class? Bottom. There's no - there's no - I weren't in middle class. Right at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8008749\charrsid3812201 bottom}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Who would you say were the middle class people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well them as get - a good wage. Them as get a good wage. They keep saying so many out of work don't they, you hear it on telly. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8008749\charrsid3812201 Well this quarter - quarter doesn't want work so he has to sort out of t'other half. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
There's quarters everywhere. You can see on the telly when -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Who were the middle class people when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well them that - as get a good wage. Got a good wage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 And you would be able to tell a difference in the homes and what else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye, their wage you know, their ways, they could go Blackpool and - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8008749\charrsid3812201 
Morecombe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  or anything like that. We couldn't. We couldn't go, no, impossible, we never dreamt about it. Apart from me eldest brother walked it to Blackpool once.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 From here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye. He walked it to Blackpool. He did. Yes he did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 He was determined to see Blackpool?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye, he walked it. And he had nothing. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1051900\charrsid3812201 He had walked it back to. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye, aye. Aye, he was raring to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 How old would he be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 He were married. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Would it be before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Do you ever remember being brought up to treat some people differently to others, you told me you touched your cap to Mr Topp?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh aye. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you call them sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Not - no, we called them sir - we'd say good morning, raise our cap to these two ladies or Mr Topp you see and as boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What was Mr Topp, he was very important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Bit - a big factory master. Farnworth. Armitage and Topps. And Armitage - that were - Mr Topp's wife was Armitage and Armitage, his house is there now and it's a home for poor people as ill - for people is poor. It belongs to Bolton and we had a fel
low here, he come from -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 But as a boy you always thought of Mr Topp as very important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh yes, yes. Oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Who else was important in the district where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well - I knowed a fellow called Mr Billinew, was - he was not the head
master but next and I remember we used to take these homers, homing pigeons in baskets when they were going to France. He was the secretary, and he used to look down how many you had and all like that you know in our baskets. Register 'em you see, and man
 
as had the pigeons he had to pay and Mr Billinew were the under man to being teacher, the headmaster. He were rum boy, he would - he'd have a joke with us. And the vicar was a very nice fellow, Mr Wilson he were called in our days. Very good man. Very goo
d man. He talked to us like me talking to you, see, he would.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Do you remember your mother or dad being referred to as sir or madam or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No. No. I do, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You remember the class distinction, tell me about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well - 
myself I always thought I was good as anybody living. And I was good as Queen. And I'll talk to Queen if she come here, I can talk to anybody. You have free speech in this country and I'll talk to anybody that'll listen, I don't care who they are if I tal
k
 - I thought with some of them, oh yes, some thought they were up here and we were down there but time - I used to say, time will tell. We'll get level with these people sometime. Time will tell, we's come up and we knows what we're doing, you know, and w
e did, so -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Do you remember anybody in the district being referred to as a real lady and why was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Well - that old lady as - fetched children in the world, they called here a good old lady. No one - there's not two - but anybody up the village.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Because she was kind you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Yes. Yes. She wasn't a nurse, she wasn't a real nurse - she wasn't a - district nurse nor nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did she have to be paid for doing this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 If you could give her a copper or two she'd have it, if you couldn't - it were just same. She didn't bother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 She didn't mind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No, no, no. No, I remember quite well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Do you remember anyone being referred to as a real gentleman?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well - I don't know as I can say that. I don't know as I can, a real gentleman in the village. No. No, I can't. Anyhow -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Were some people thought of as rough and some respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Can you tell me about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What was the difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh well, I've lived in one of them
 streets but not in the club. I've lived in one of them streets. They thought they owned the village, some of people who lived in. Now, I'll tell - I'll tell you, this is God's truth. Now we never were drinkers as I've told you, but one day, I hadn't been
 in this village long - long, I'd just saw these fellows say, where are you going? I said, I'm going - he says, come on, let's go and have a gill at this pub, you know. Well really what he meant I were can, you know what can is?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You were paying?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Yes, I know, and so - anyway we went in this little pub and it was a box like - a little box, and landlady had clogs on, landlady at back of vault. There was three chaps sit here at back, you know. And I think they've been in all afternoon, I think they -
 they were, you know. So I goes to bar and I had a soft hat on and I says, two beers please. One of these fellows says, I'll knock his hat off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Let's see, 1920.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 This man didn't fight fair, he'd jump on the table and kick you in the face?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye, if he'd chance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 And he was a big fighter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 He were the fighter -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1051900\charrsid3812201 fighter}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  in the village. And I could have knocked him for a sixer if it had been a strange place. Then before he wakened up I could have done but I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 He was champion out of Darcy Lever, did you go to live in Darcy Lever then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye. Aye. That belonged to Bolton you know, it's next door. Anyhow a week or two after I'm going - I lives in Bolton, a man says hello.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 The policeman fastened him on a cart?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 On cart. Wheel him to Town Hall and then at Monday he's in the box.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 How would he fasten him to the cart?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 To take him to Town Hall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Strap him down or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8008749\charrsid3812201 Tied him}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
 down 'cos he were - rough. He's in the 
box at Monday. A man in the box said, oh, he says, we've had a wild animal running about in the village for a lot of years, so we thought we'd send a lion tamer down to tame him and - that were - fined a pound - fined a pound.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 This policeman was the lion tamer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye. And that were how I had to leave it, he never come out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you see a lot of the police as a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Yes, oh no, oh aye, I knew a lot of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 How did they treat the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Not too bad. Not too bad, not like they a
re today you know, they - if you were in the wrong they'd give you a clout with their cape and you were off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Were you afraid of a policeman, did your mother says she'd bring a policeman if you were naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No, no, never afraid of them, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You think he was all right with the people do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Well they're not so bad, they'd have a chat with you. And this last chief - not - chief as left and went to Sheffield for - regular duty, his idea, don't kiss 'em but have a word with them as you se
e. You'll get more information off them than what you will off anybody else, and that were his idea, you know. Don't put your nose at 'em when you see 'em every day, no, hello how are you going on and you get more information off them. He used say that th
at chief.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Were you frightened of policeman as a boy though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
No. No, no, no, they weren't bad I'll tell you did you did wrong they'd - hit you with a cape or - don't dare do wrong but that th'end of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 In the district where you lived suppos
e someone did something that the neighbours didn't like how would they treat them, how would they show their disapproval?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 They - they - they'd be sent - sent them - they'd tell police when he come up, there were no going to police station unless it w
ere something very serious, they'd wait for him coming and tell him what he'd been doing, and then he - he'd find him and give him a good thrashing, tell him do it again now. You'll catch it. Well they just let him go their own way. Used to let - let 'em 
go their own way. They know they said - they know their own way, I mean, they - they'll come through one way or another. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Didn't they show their disapproval in any other way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Your home was rented wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you ever see your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Yes, landlady.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 How did she treat you, what did you think of her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Well my mother used to draw the rents for all road and then hand it, hand 'em in every so often and she could let 'em and - if any come empty
. And - but she got nothing for it. Only thank you. Aye. Used to let th'houses if any come empty and she used collect rents. They practically nearly all fetched them to her if they didn't she went for 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What did your mother think of the landlady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 All right. Her were quite honest her had that big shop }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1051900\charrsid3812201 now}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  across the town now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 When you were young who do you think the shopkeepers mixed with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 The shopkeepers? When I were young? Well - they sorted in with people, they had to do }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1051900\charrsid3812201 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  deal with 'em.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Who do you think the teachers mixed with socially?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Who? Well no, no, they didn't mix when the school was over. No, they just kept to their own lot you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What about parsons, who did they mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well - they did come down a visiting and they would speak and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1051900\charrsid3812201 nod}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  to you if they were passing anytime. They would speak to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 But do you remember who they mixed with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well I don't say they mixed really with the people after only just going in visiting something like t
hat or just speaking in the street or move to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Who would the employers mix with do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Well - you see, they were - same as I tell you, they - they were a different class mixed with all the tip - top dogs you know, 'cos all their famil
y, they'd married in - Doctor Marsh was Armitage, Topp's wife was Armitage. Doctor Marsh's brother married a Ramsey, th'pit owners and they were all locked in - all locked together you see. Well them were really - the pals, all up together you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 They were who you considered the upper class were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye, oh yes, all locked in one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Who was the most important person that you knew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well - I liked Mr Topp he was very - he were gentleman. Oh yes, he were gentleman. He was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Why do you think he was a gentleman, because of his money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8008749\charrsid3812201 Well, no, he - no he were very nice and - he didn't turn his face when he saw you know, he - he'd recognise you, you know. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Were only boy but he recognised you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Do you remember the type of people who went to church and the type of people who went to chapel and was there any difference between them?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No, I - now I'll tell you this. It's not altogether the church or the chapels you want is it, some goes to the nearest - if their not Cat
holics. Now Catholics will go to their now, no matter how far it is. But we'll say Wesleyans, Church of England. You live near Wesleyans you'll go to that. You live near t'other you'll go to that 'cos it's been proved in my family. Now you see, we lived u
p Highfield Road where the family is where we went to Peel School. Now eventually come to top end of villages - village well, Morton school were near, my two sisters went there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You went to the same school all the time though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 I went same school
 we kept it up but the never - because they lived nearer Morton so they went to Warton. And that same with lot of church and chapels, which is nearest you see, bar Catholics. I'm not saying they won't go, they will go -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Do you remember any prejudice against Catholics when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Well, I've had 'em - dealed with 'em, there's some good people again but - they're frightened of Father. They're frightened of the Father. They are now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 But when you were a boy they were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Yes. Yes. The
y are - they are, yes, they are. If there used to be bother along Deansgate at Bolton any bother they didn't send for police. He sent for Father. They were nearly all Irish. As soon as they saw him they stopped - dead. Frightened of him. They are today. T
hey are today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Do you think your father and mother had the same attitude to people in different classes and different walks of life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Yes, I think they had, they always - they recognized - they said who were good and who were good and who was not 
good in any class, you know, they had 'em all taped who were decent, you know, to us and to the worker, in any - at any time you know they'd say that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What class do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well I can't say but what she
 - she must be in the lowest class because she was scratching all her life in a sense. You know what that is. She was scratching all days of her life in a sense.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Your parents were always very poor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Always very poor 'til we all started working and then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 How did you feel about it, them having a job to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 They were hard times - they were hard times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You never had to go to anyone for any help?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No. We did not. We could have done - we could have done with doing but 
we didn't and were plenty beside me couldn't - could have done with it. But couldn't - wouldn't - they'd do it - they'd die before we'd do it because they come and examine what you had afore you could get anything you know, you went what they called on th
e Guardians. Oh you hadn't to ride on a car and you hadn't to do this and you hadn't to do t'other so you were best away, I mean if you could have managed - if you could have managed on dry bread you were best away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 As a child how did you feel about being so poor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Well - well you see we'd known no different, it were our world as we'd had to live in, brought up in, we didn't know no different, you know. Just catch as catch can as they say, we didn't know no different. No. I've had better food and m
ore food here than I've ever had in me life and more comfortable food. I have. I tell you, I went to me sister - when I lived with me sister I were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You mean your sisters grew up very careful with food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 And they kept the light off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Aye, they're saving up now and they're on pension on ten pound a week and it's their own house, they're saving up. In fact I bet they're saving up now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 The Lord knows.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You think this is because you were so poor as children they don't know anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Aye. No, no. Well I tell you, when I went home in winter, specially at seven o'clock, I had the key, back door'd be barred, paper under back door so as no mice could get in and if I happened to go out at back they used to 
tell me in morning I'd shifted that paper hadn't put it down right. I hadn't put it down right. Lord bless me. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8008749\charrsid3812201 
And when it come dark they'd have time on radio, she does that, oh, we're not wasting electric. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Off. Off. Right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You think this is the result of being so poor do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 I've never seen no difference. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Your mother was married at twenty-eight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye. But I don't know how old she were when the oldest boy was born but there was eighteen months in us. Eighteen months older than 
me but I don't know what age she was when he was born, how long she'd been married but she was twenty-eight when she was married.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 How old was your father when he was married, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 There were - there were only six months in 'em. Six year old, I remember him being buried.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 At Highfield Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Yes. Well then we got a fellow coming living next door and how this Saturday he used to have a pint of mild and he wanted fight. Every Saturday night when he'd had a lot of drink. So - father
 were on three days a week and he challenged father one - one night, had so much you know, had something to drink. So father said, well, I can't afford to fight to night but, he said, when I've a play day you must get your fighting clothes on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 When he'd had a pay day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
When he had a play day - that's time off. He says, to fellow, get your fighting clothes on, you know. So it comes this day and never bothered. So me mother sent word to me grandma, Manchester Road East, to her sister at Manchester R
oad West, if a house comes empty let her know. We were getting away. And it comes Manchester Road West from em mother's sister, me auntie, so -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You were actually born at Highfield road were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 I was born at Highfield Road.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You were telling me you left this house because that man was always making a noise and he used to fight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Wanted a fight, yes, so - it were Manchester Road East or West we must go and me mother, that were me auntie got house empty West so then we went there, that's
 where we finished up. That's were finished up in four - in a big - big house, three and four a week. Three and four a week, that's it. And they built }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8008749\charrsid3812201 Dennis's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  farm when I was up there, he was a Quaker you know, Dennis. He's a Quaker yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You weren't a Quaker were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
No. But - one fellow says to me, you live in a Quaker home, are you a Quaker? No, I said, I'm same road as wind, I'm a Calethumpian. Do you know? Anything for - anything same way as the wind, where it's going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you know any Quakers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
No, I only remember this Dennis, I never heard tell of him after that, all them years. All them years, never tell of him. He said it were a Quakers home and I didn't know, but I can't find nothing wrong with 'em. Now listen, God's truth, th
ey - they don't drink, they don't believe in fighting. Well - who does.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 After you left Manchester Road West you went to another area of Bolton didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Darcy Lever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Where did you live then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well I lived in a street called Motor Str
eet, it's pulled down now. It's pulled down now. Yes. And - in my time down there, that were up to 1928 there were forty percent had candle power for their light. Down there, it's only little town. They were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 They were so poor you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 They were, and you washed every Sunday, not at Monday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
The Lord knows, I don't know. They called it Dolly Tub City through that. Aye. That's what they called it, they washed at Sunday. Oh they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Tell me about the poverty as you remember it as a child in your own words?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Well same as I tell you, we had to scratch for what extra food as you wanted, we had to scratch. Never saw any supper at home, you know. never. Don't remember ever having a supper at home when I was a boy. There were no
ne. If they hadn't gone to bed mother and father and if we come back there's nothing for us. There were none. We had to scramble what we could outside, you know, earning any coppers buy some.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Were all your friends in the same position?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Nearly al
l in the same position. I tell you, we - I've seen fifty stood at corner, not a penny in their hands, it's summer, they couldn't help it. Couldn't help it. No. You see, because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did no one in Bolton come to help, there was no means of relief at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
No, only Guardians as they called it and people were half clemmed before they'd go to it because they come and watch you and - inspected this and you went on. Inspected everything before you got - oh and you hadn't to ride on a car and you hadn't to 
do this and you hadn't - oh - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Do you know anyone who ever went to the Guardians?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 I did. My eldest brother had to do. She'd three girls, one -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Was this before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Yes. My eldest - my niece - they'll be coming here tomorrow, it's 
middlemost of the three girls of me oldest brother and she'll be coming and a girl and there's one young niece didn't know her father only eight months, you can tell, these other two - these other girls, neither of them were working. Right you are - she h
ad to have some.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 She had to go to the Guardians?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Eventually th'oldest started working a bit, she started coming seeing me and then as she scrambled off it - she scrambled off it and she died, mother, so these t'other two was growing up and they w
orked together these three and lived together 'til eventually they all three married. And her husband's a postman as is coming to see me. And the other works in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 When this lady did go to the Guardians how did they treat her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 They don't treat 'em so good I'll tell you. They come and examine what you had in th'houses is worth anything for start with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Looking back people say it was the good old days, did you think so?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 They're nothing but stories. It's only lies - nothing of the sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 How do you think of it then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 It were - if they put this instead of the good old days, you put bad old - bad old days - that'll do, that'll fit proper. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8008749\charrsid3812201 Some of them turns as comes on the telly they go in the good old days as they call it but put in the - put in bad old days instead of good old days it'd be more right then what that is.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 When you were growing up did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well - little bit. Aye, I've been to meetings, oh aye, used to like going or sales, any sale
s, I mean to say I bought anything. Used to like going sales and been to meeting. I once hear a vicar say - the Lord give the land to the people. Not to a certain few as had it. Once heard a vicar say that. He did, at a meeting. Reverend Wilcox.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you follow your dad in being Labour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
I had to do because I always had to work. I went out to work. I've been a worker, well - I'm not going for them as - now look at - I saw an M.P. -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You mean you're not voting for the people who are the bosses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
They've ruled us too long. They were communists, you daren't talk to plenty people, but this is God's truth, before we were born the communists ruled this country. They were the lords. They won every time - they won, they ruled the country so they we
re communists, where did they come to own all these grounds can you tell me. There's nobody can answer me that. There's Lord Ellesmere, there's Lord Kenyou, there's Lord Bradford, there's Lord Derby, Lady Beaulieu, they own all this ground, where'd they g
et it from. They say king give it 'em, I say well Queen should have took it off 'em and let it come to state. It should. No betting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you feel any of this as a boy, did you feel resentful about being poor, as you were growing up and went into the pits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Tell me about your days in the pit when you first started, how you felt about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
I didn't feel upset about it because we'd never lived no other way. We never lived no other - but I know in '14 war there were thousands as went a
s were glad to go you know, they'd no need to gone some 'cos they were - they were ages, they wouldn't have called them up. They were glad to go because they were only existing. I had a home uncle went with houseful of children, glad to go. He went to the
 '14 war and then he come back and got killed in pit. Yes, glad to go. You see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Tell me about when your brother was killed in the pit, what happened at home, how your mother took it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh - bad. Bad. They fetched 'em home them days, didn't take 'e
m mortuary you know. No, no, no, no, I can see - I can see the under manager now, it weren't far from pit, I can see him leading the ambulance down the road and up the street with his knee - bosses used to have kneecaps on you know, same as horses had.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 For kneeling. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Why did they have to kneel a lot, the bosses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well we had - when they was coming to visiting you and - we had 'em. Only twenty-one inch where I worked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You were on your knees all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh yes. Well they had them 'cos it -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Who do you refer to as the bosses - the foreman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 The under manager.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You don't mean the pit owner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No, no. No, no. Never seen the pit owner, never - there were manager, under manager and firemen. Firemen - goes 
rounds. Oh no. Well I can see him now, he's dead. And I see him coming down the lane, up the street with his leading the ambulance. Carry him upstairs and doctor were there in a few minutes. And he knew he said to - oh I heard my father say to him in the 
other room, how is he doctor? He said, he's better off. Better off. That were all. We never seen him. He was mangled with eleven tubs and there was nobody there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 He was mangled did you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 With eleven tubs. Should have - the idea, there was nobo
dy there but his top toe was broke and they think he'd been leaning over which had to take this pit prop and he must have getting his foot fast and getting dragged under. And we never saw him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 And you only got forty pounds?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Forty pound. That was - 'cos had a father and weren't dependent on, that's what they said.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 How did you work down the pit as a boy, what clothes did you wear?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well - well at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8008749\charrsid3812201 Sandown}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  I had a pair of little }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8008749\charrsid3812201 knocks}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  on and me clogs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Your pair of knickers and your togs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8008749\charrsid3812201 Sandown}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
. And it were like a furnace. And we never got a drink only what were lukewarm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What did you take down for food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Water. Oh food? Jam and bread - if mice hadn't took it. Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 The mice at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Down there were h
undreds, with it being Walkden pit, hundreds. They go down in the props, in the timber then they breed with it being so hot. There were hundreds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 And they used to pinch your food when you were a boy in the pit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 When I were a man never mind a boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 But when you were a boy before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye. You see, when you - when you were having your breakfast, you'd no breakfast like this and that's why you see - have you ever seen }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8008749\charrsid3812201 colliers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  in buses sit down? Well they sit -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 They sit on their haunches?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well - that's it. Now you see if they sit down down pit unless they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8008749\charrsid3812201 get}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  a board which they hadn't always a board they're back could be in the sharp end of the stone what you built so they sit away from it and sit like that. Yes. Now then, at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8008749\charrsid3812201 Sandown}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
 your foods there, you sit like that and if you wink your eye, mice - they're all playing round you, and you wink your eye and they're at 'em. They're at it. And then if they did find it you used like hang it up on a rope and if they did find it they'
d go through the paper, through the red handkerchief, through the lot to eat middle. You'd know they'd been, they didn't take bit off sides, straight through the soft part. And it was swarmed with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 And you didn't dare even to put it down to pause for a minute?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You - what - they were playing round you. They were playing round you.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Didn't the bosses ever do anything about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You couldn't do, there were that many. They bred like - ooh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did they eve try to get rid of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
No. Some used get killed you know and sometimes we'd take a little trap, catch one or two but that couldn't clear 'em, there were that many. Were that many.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Tell me about your life as a boy down the pit though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well when I start, at thirteen 
I started riding tubs as the hooker, they called them, see they shove the tubs in at one side and the man at this side pulls the empties out you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8008749\charrsid3812201 
Then we boys, me and another fellow, used to ride them around, hook 'em up and then when they'd a full load for to go up they moved, you follow me, well I weren't on that long before I went a pony driving or gell driving what they call it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 There were some bonny }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8008749\charrsid3812201 ponies}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
 at work. So I have go on then right to the end, a mile and a half in with these ponies, mile and a half and they know their job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 The ponies did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Yes. They did. They know their job, well I started gell driving but the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Gal driving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 The ponies - they call them gals. They call them - aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No, they called gals not girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Gals is a Lancashire term for girls isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye, but gals, they call them gals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Why gals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 I don't know, they didn't call them ponies, the pit gals used to call them. Anyhow - and I'll never forget this as long as I live. 
There were - there were one called Lily, a biggish one, and as good and quiet as - gold. Real good. Then they'd one called Tommy, a grey one. He could be awkward if he wanted. Well sometimes I had Tommy and you see, me - the - the shop was here, that's wh
ere the tubs comes to go to the pit and then I was down what they call a lower side to take to these men. I used to hook them up for this Tommy take down and as he's coming round the corner I used to ask scotches to put in the - in the wheels so -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What are scotches?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Piece of wood or piece iron to - to make the wheels slur, not go round. Like putting a brake on. Aye, well - well going too fast I don't get any in, so these tubs are bang about, but what do you think Tommy did? Gal - pony. He put its
 bottom agen em, he were holding them back and when it got down he moved to one side and - tipple over, --- Clever. Then and this were the worst thing that ever happened, I were frightened to death. I were only a lad. We used to come op this lower side tw
os and threes -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You think Tommy did it deliberately?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 He did it to save himself, he knowed - he knowed what he were doing, he were holding 'em back. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8008749\charrsid3812201 If they'd have got him he'd have gone down the dump.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You mean they'd have pushed him down and killed him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Aye. But he - he had his back in 'em. So anyhow but this were worst that ever happened. Now there's one - I'm first, I'm leader, we're two and you were supposed to have - they call 'em billies, it's a - you put it on the axle and it draw
s up as you go only you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1051900\charrsid3812201 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  back it was sticking on floor and hold em and you're supposed put -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Like an anchor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye. You supposed to put one on every time. Well I'm the leading lad, t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1051900\charrsid3812201 
\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 others are coming up with some and I've 2 tubs with Tommy. I for
got to put me billy on. Some tubs we get filled in, never bother. And he stops, and he looks round. And sometime he go with sausing (scalding) sometimes he go with coaxing. What will I do. So I begin "Ah, he's a good lad', Ah - Tommy's a good lad' and off
 he sets with it if he hadn't if he stood a bit he'd have backed back. He'd have smashed into em. I never forgot it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Why were you always afraid of the tubs tipping over - because they would have killed you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 They would have killed the others, I were at front leading the way, the other ponies were coming at the back of him.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You mean they'd have killed the other ponies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 They'd kill the men at the bottom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No, the ponies as were coming up at the back of him, then if he'd
 have backed back it would have hit the other pony and then there tubs was there bang - oh yes, never forget it. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you ever see this happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No, I've never seen it happen, some near shades with 'em but I never seen it happen. They all com
e out all right when the pit finished. Mind you, they go blind but they're fed well, Oh they're fed -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 They were better than the men weren't they, you only had bread and jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 They were better than - th'horse on top. They were all in good conditio
n. Oh yes, they're all good. They used to have a parade at Monday morning when they've been in stable all weekend. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You'd have a parade with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Yes, the - they paraded theirself. We had them dancing about you know. As much as to say 'hello'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 They were always kept down below though were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye, yes. Some pits used to wind 'em up periodically but they didn't here where I worked at. Oh they were good. And then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You never drank tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Only at one station, I didn't care for it so I never had no more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What did you drink as a boy at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 More water than anything. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Even with meals would you have water?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye, never bothered. Either a drink before or after when I were thirsty. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Your dad had tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh me dad did, aye, but I didn't bother. I'd sup - I've drank more coffee since I've come over here then what I did before and I buy it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Tell me what your memories are, looking back, of your mum and dad.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh I've had a few years with one or two of them. I had to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 When you were at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye, and since I've went from school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 As a boy do you remember some families being thought of as rough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh yes. I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Why were they called this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 I don't know how you could see it. I don't know how you could see it. I'd
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Pieces of wood of piece iron too - to make the wheels slur (slide) not go round. Like putting a brake on. Aye well - were going to fast, I don't gat any in, so these tubs are banging about, but 
what do you think Tommy did? Gal - Pony? He put his bottom again 'em he were holding em back and when it got down he moved at one side and they tipple over - clever! Then - that were the worst thing they ever happened (meant could ever happen). I were fri
g
htened to death (in case tub tipped or slipped). I were only a lad. We used to come up lower side in twos or threes. He meant that if the truck ran away whoever was following would get killed, the pony knew this and if the tub banged used to put his botto
m to it and tip it over to stop it running away! But would step sideways himself to avoid it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Well - I - I will say me mother were one of the best. And were very tall smart woman. Very tall and smart and good. But she had work hard. She's had work har
d and they agreed, agreed, they agreed quite you know, just like Darby and Joan, they did. They were good. Oh me mother - one of the best. No better.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 And your dad too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye, he weren't too bad, beyond six as I told you, but she were as good as gold. She were. No better. Ninety-two mind you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 When she died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye. And a little sore come here, gangrene.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What year did she die?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Eeh I do forget. I do forget. Eeh I forget but - she did anything she was fair and square above board.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 How old was your father when he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 He were only about seventy-four. That's all he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 That's still a good age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye. Seventy-four them days, seventy-four were good age weren't it. Years back seventy - oh you're an old chap. They used 
say that you know. Aye. Seventy. Oh aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Do you remember any of your pals at school being considered rough or some respectable and some rough and why?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 This stitched when I was a boy - can you see a mark. Well, we were playing at something in sc
hoolyard and there was a wall, stone wall you know, and then there were pillar stuck out like only so far. And one fellow knocked me in there. And that were cut and they didn't - I didn't know my doctor to tell him how old I were. He'd known every dock st
r
ike and remember teaching taking me bottom of Clyde Lane to a doctor called Doctor Martin, he stitched it, he wasn't me doctor but she said I was a boy. Having a bit of a rough do, he knocked me there. I mustn't have been so old because I couldn't tell yo
u name of the doctor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Do you remember families who were thought of as rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Oh aye, oh aye, I find - I know them people, I know a lot of them. Well - it - it's hard to say but this fellow I known him and he used be a rough handful at wresting in his day, rough handle at wrestling you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 This was as he was growing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 As a man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Was this before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 I - aye, he was a bit rough but he was a man he were kind of all in - not all in wrestler, proper wrestler. But - when we wen
t to Bolton if we'd money at Monday night -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 This was before 1918 as you were growing up was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Finest two lads - on the lane to my home as is - he gets off top of lane - this wasn't on the same train but what's happened I knowed the man as had 
a little shop there and he know him to. So he called going and knocking for some cigarettes. She says as he went - went aside and the police did him, hit one helmet with his mallet. Did him one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 He said he were breaking in. Listen. So 
this Billy being strong, what do you think he did? He got hold of him and bumped him and throwed him }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1051900\charrsid3812201 o'er}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  th'edge - }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1051900\charrsid3812201 sergeant}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 . So he got pinched. They said the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1051900\charrsid3812201 sergeant}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  was left over the hedge to die, all bunkum and he runs down Farnworth with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1051900\charrsid3812201 sergeant\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  truncheon in his hands, this fellow, his leg beat him. He appealed and appealed and tried and he got ten years. And he swore -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Yet the policeman had attacked him first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1051900\charrsid3812201 Aye but he said he were breaking in and sweared to his maker he was not but hit police, he molested policeman.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 And he still got ten years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 He still got ten years and he wanted join up when the war was on, they wouldn't let him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 This was the first war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye. Well this policeman when he retired he come a keeping 
a pub at Little Hulton. And the Bill could never forget or forgive. He were afraid to go out. He was afraid to go out. They didn't patronise him he were afraid to go out. They'd never forgive anything - and there's been a strike on there you know when any
body's worked on quiet - blacklegs, they're pointed out as long as they live. They're pointed at as long as they live, they never forgive 'em. No. They wouldn't have 'em. Last pit as I worked at you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1051900\charrsid3812201 Sandown}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  and I worked there -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1051900\charrsid3812201 Sandown}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  was Farnworth wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
No. Swinton. Swinton. Just out of Walkden, Swinton. Well I worked with this fellow and he were secretary over a pitman club and - they - they're due for going away when he says to landlady he says, what about our teas for next week on S
aturday? Says I've booked, everything's all right. He says, aye, what about these five as can't go? Why, he said, nobody's never told me. She says, I'm telling you, there's five as doesn't go with us or else we don't go with them. He says, why? We don't g
o with any }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1051900\charrsid3812201 k}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 nobsticks, they go theirself or we go ourselves, what are you doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1051900\charrsid3812201 k}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
nobsticks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 People is blacklegs, you know how blacklegs. They call them knobsticks. They hadn't to go with 'em. They wouldn't go with '}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1051900\charrsid3812201 em, they wouldn't, never forget \rquote em}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
 Long as they live. But do you see where they're beat when there's a pit strike they allowed safety men to go down - aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Do you remember a strike before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 I can tell you. I did. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Tell me about it, you were in it were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No, I were in 1921.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Can you remember one before 1918?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
'18. Well not really - a real strike but I've heard me father talk how there's been big strike years and years afore when you used to go to Oldham where they was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1051900\charrsid3812201 begging}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  bread in the strike.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1051900\charrsid3812201 Oldham}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye. That - when mills were working, begging bread for strikers. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 That's in your father's day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Aye. Now in this last strike, '26, I helped to run a food kitchen. I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What else do you remember your father telling you about the strike before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Well - there were two or three lived in the village and they were pointed at forever. And they used to say, that's one gone, there's only two left now, as worked. They had 'em pointed as long as they lived, t
hey never forgive 'em. No, they're always there on their black books. Never forgive 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Your father was in the strike was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh aye. Aye. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You'd all be children then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh yes. Oh we wouldn't be so old but I remember him talking a
bout it many and many a time. But this last strike - well, this '26 strike I helped to run a food -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 During the strike they got half a loaf per child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Nine - aye, aye. Two once of margarine and two ounces of cheese. That were first - only had that one do you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Do you never remember your father being out of work when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Can you remember the time during these strike what happened as a child when your father was on strike?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No, no, I don't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You never remember him being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No. No, no. No. No. No, I remember '21 and the '26. I've only heard him talk about it you know. No. I only heard him talk about it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You say when you were a child all the people borrowed clothes for funerals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
They had to do, if you had a decent suit they - that suit when my brother got killed and I got a nice blue suit I lent it about a dozen times. I did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 For funerals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You didn't mind lending it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well it - they swop
ped us bread for it, they fetched it back funeral when funeral were over, yes. Oh yes. You hadn't suit you couldn't buy - suits no, and when that happened (brothers death and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid414996 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 40 compensation) it were a God send - well not - well - I got a suit through that but - well - I wouldn't have got one!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 This is the only time you had a good suit was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
Well, that were best suit I got in my life - it was some blue like a suit I have in there. Yes, oh yes. That last. I had to be careful with it. Oh yes. I w
ere - having me suit and having me holidays and looking for me holidays. This is sixty-five. Aye. And you - you - they had a fund, masters, and when all half crowns were done that went to somebody dying, you give them half a crown a week. And if all th'ha
lf crowns were out you had to wait had to wait to somebody dying afore you got yours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 They'd only so many half crowns a week they could allow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 That' all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Who owned the pit you worked in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Lord Ellesmere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 You never saw him as a person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Never saw him in me life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 He never came near the pit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
No. Well, you see, there were so much for that but if you come to be sixty five and all them half crowns you had to wait to one dying afore you got it. You see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did your father get the half crown a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well he were turned seventy and he went for men - for men then, check weighing, called check weighing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 How old did he work 'til?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Well he did it till he were seventy. Only sitting down j
ob but - pit closed shortly after, he'd have to finish. But he were getting tired, he - he - he'd practically had enough he said, practically had enough. No, that's all he did and the firemen, I had uncle, he did fifty-seven years a fireman, that's next t
o th'under manager.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Who were the bosses you actually saw as a boy though in the pit? You didn't see Lord Ellesmere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Never. There were manager, undermanager and then this fireman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 What was the manager like, was he a good sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No, I'll tell you what he were, he were Scotsman and he were called John }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1051900\charrsid3812201 
Willie}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201  Rostrum, his wife was one of the whisky people. Right. Now listen, I'm only a boy and working with these two chaps same as I told you. Well - sometimes your booking were wrong, you foll
ow me, on - on your wage. Hey - hey, we're four bob short here. Come on. And it were only hundred }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1051900\charrsid3812201 yard}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
 away in my house where we lived, what had been an old farm I remember it. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 He lived there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 No, he - over a big - over a big gate they sho
ved me. Daren't come away till he makes thee - a paper out, petty cash. Aye. What do you want? I say, we're short of money Mr. Rostrum. What's you number? Number ninety-nine. He says, that numbers stamped on my chest. He said, I'll make it right next week
.
 I says, no we want it this week. I'll make it right next week. I said, we want - they told me say I mustn't come away, I had to have it this week. Do you know what he say as he gets paper out, damn, you and I go to the house and get petty cash. Aye. Aye.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Four bob would be a lot wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Oh aye, aye, wait 'till next week. No. They told me definite I mustn't come away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 They always sent you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2691140 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Always shoved me o'er gate. He'd gone ho, he were at home then you see. And there only 5 in t
'pit and I'm in is home really. But I had to stop there }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1051900\charrsid3812201 till}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 
 he made a paper out of petty cash. No betting. Think he meant here there were only 5 from his home in the pit at that time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11620878 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6691798\charrsid3812201 Did you like him as a person though?
